Vice President Biden expresses his sorrow and sense of loss upon hearing about the passing of Archbishop Pietro Sambi, the Apostolic Nuncio to the United States. He praises Archbishop Sambi's friendship, counsel, empathy, and comfort that he brought to many lives. Biden also admires Archbishop Sambi's distinguished diplomatic service for the Roman Catholic Church in various regions around the world. He mentions that Archbishop Sambi was highly respected by all Americans who had the opportunity to meet him during his travels throughout the country. The Vice President extends his condolences and prayers to Archbishop Sambi's family and friends.